body:
The Regions API provides information about available deployment regions, capacity, and regional features. This reference covers region queries and regional resource management.

List Regions:

GET /regions

Returns all available regions:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "us-east-1",
      "name": "US East (Virginia)",
      "location": {
        "country": "United States",
        "city": "Virginia",
        "latitude": 38.13,
        "longitude": -78.45
      },
      "status": "available",
      "features": ["high_availability", "backup_replication"]
    }
  ]
}

Get Region Details:

GET /regions/{region_id}

Returns detailed region information including:
- Availability zones
- Supported deployment sizes
- Feature availability
- Current capacity status

Example:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "id": "us-east-1",
    "name": "US East (Virginia)",
    "availability_zones": [
      {"id": "us-east-1a", "status": "available"},
      {"id": "us-east-1b", "status": "available"},
      {"id": "us-east-1c", "status": "available"}
    ],
    "supported_sizes": ["small", "medium", "large", "xlarge"],
    "capacity_status": "normal",
    "features": {
      "high_availability": true,
      "backup_replication": true,
      "point_in_time_recovery": true
    }
  }
}

Region Capacity:

GET /regions/{region_id}/capacity

Check current capacity availability:

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "region": "us-east-1",
    "capacity_status": "normal",
    "available_sizes": ["small", "medium", "large"],
    "constrained_sizes": ["xlarge"],
    "last_updated": "2024-09-15T10:30:00Z"
  }
}

Capacity statuses:
- normal: All sizes available
- constrained: Some sizes limited
- full: No capacity available

Region Pricing:

GET /regions/{region_id}/pricing

Query parameters:
- size: Deployment size
- currency: Currency code (default USD)

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "region": "us-east-1",
    "currency": "USD",
    "pricing": [
      {
        "size": "small",
        "hourly_rate": 0.50,
        "monthly_estimate": 360.00
      },
      {
        "size": "medium",
        "hourly_rate": 1.00,
        "monthly_estimate": 720.00
      }
    ]
  }
}

Region Latency:

GET /regions/latency

Measure latency to all regions:

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "source_ip": "203.0.113.42",
    "regions": [
      {
        "region": "us-east-1",
        "latency_ms": 15,
        "status": "reachable"
      },
      {
        "region": "eu-west-1",
        "latency_ms": 85,
        "status": "reachable"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Region Features:

GET /regions/features

Compare feature availability across regions:

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "features": [
      {
        "name": "high_availability",
        "regions": ["us-east-1", "us-west-2", "eu-west-1", "eu-central-1"]
      },
      {
        "name": "point_in_time_recovery",
        "regions": ["us-east-1", "eu-west-1"]
      }
    ]
  }
}

Region Maintenance:

GET /regions/{region_id}/maintenance

View scheduled maintenance:

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "maint-abc123",
      "region": "us-east-1",
      "type": "infrastructure_upgrade",
      "scheduled_start": "2024-09-20T02:00:00Z",
      "scheduled_end": "2024-09-20T04:00:00Z",
      "impact": "Brief connectivity interruption possible"
    }
  ]
}

Region Quotas:

GET /regions/{region_id}/quotas

View regional resource quotas:

Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "region": "us-east-1",
    "quotas": {
      "max_deployments": 100,
      "current_deployments": 15,
      "max_storage_gb": 10000,
      "current_storage_gb": 250
    }
  }
}

The official NovaCLI JavaScript SDK provides a modern, Promise-based interface to the NovaCLI API for Node.js and browser environments. This reference covers installation, configuration, and usage patterns.

Installation:

NPM:
npm install @novacli/sdk

Yarn:
yarn add @novacli/sdk

CDN (browser):
<script src="https://cdn.novacli.io/sdk/v1/novacli.min.js"></script>

Requires Node.js 16+ or modern browser with ES6 support.

Basic Setup:

CommonJS:
const { NovaCLI } = require('@novacli/sdk');

const client = new NovaCLI({
  apiKey: 'nova_sk_abc123...'
});

ES6 Modules:
import { NovaCLI } from '@novacli/sdk';

const client = new NovaCLI({
  apiKey: process.env.NOVACLI_API_KEY
});

Configuration Options:

const client = new NovaCLI({
  apiKey: 'nova_sk_abc123...',
  baseURL: 'https://api.novacli.io',
  timeout: 30000,
  maxRetries: 3,
  region: 'us-east-1',
  headers: {
    'X-Custom-Header': 'value'
  }
});

Deployments:

List deployments:
const deployments = await client.deployments.list({
  status: 'active',
  region: 'us-east-1',
  limit: 50
});

http://deployments.data.forEach(dep => {
  console.log(${http://dep.id}: ${http://dep.name});
});

Get deployment:
const deployment = await client.deployments.get('dep-abc123');
console.log(Status: ${deployment.status});

Create deployment:
const deployment = await client.deployments.create({
  name: 'my-deployment',
  size: 'medium',
  region: 'us-east-1',
  config: {
    maxConnections: 100,
    backupEnabled: true
  },
  tags: { env: 'production' }
});

Update deployment:
const updated = await client.deployments.update('dep-abc123', {
  size: 'large',
  config: { maxConnections: 200 }
});

Delete deployment:
await client.deployments.delete('dep-abc123', { force: false });

Backups:

List backups:
const backups = await client.backups.list('dep-abc123', {
  type: 'manual'
});

Create backup:
const backup = await client.backups.create('dep-abc123', {
  name: 'pre-migration',
  retentionDays: 90
});

Restore backup:
const restore = await client.backups.restore('dep-abc123', 'backup-xyz789', {
  verifyBeforeRestore: true
});

console.log(Restore status: ${restore.status});

Error Handling:

try {
  const deployment = await client.deployments.get('invalid-id');
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof NovaCLI.NotFoundError) {
    console.error('Deployment not found');
  } else if (error instanceof NovaCLI.AuthenticationError) {
    console.error('Authentication failed');
  } else if (error instanceof NovaCLI.RateLimitError) {
    console.error(Rate limited. Retry after ${error.retryAfter}s);
  } else {
    console.error(API error: ${error.message});
  }
}

Pagination:

Automatic pagination:
for await (const deployment of client.deployments.iterate()) {
  console.log(http://deployment.name);
}

Manual pagination:
let cursor;
do {
  const page = await client.deployments.list({
    limit: 50,
    cursor
  });

  http://page.data.forEach(dep => console.log(http://dep.name));
  cursor = page.pagination.nextCursor;
} while (cursor);

Promise Handling:

Promise chains:
client.deployments.list({ status: 'active' })
  .then(deployments => {
    console.log(Found ${http://deployments.data.length} deployments);
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.error('Error:', error.message);
  });

Async/await:
async function listDeployments() {
  try {
    const deployments = await client.deployments.list();
    return http://deployments.data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}

Streaming Logs:

Stream deployment logs:
const stream = http://client.logs.stream('dep-abc123');

stream.on('data', log => {
  console.log(${log.timestamp} [${log.level}] ${log.message});
});

stream.on('error', error => {
  console.error('Stream error:', error);
});

stream.on('end', () => {
  console.log('Stream ended');
});

Webhooks:

Create webhook:
const webhook = await client.webhooks.create({
  url: 'https://myapp.com/webhook',
  events: ['deployment.created', 'deployment.failed'],
  secret: 'webhook_secret_123'
});

Verify webhook signature:
const crypto = require('crypto');

function verifyWebhook(secret, body, signature) {
  const hmac = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret);
  hmac.update(body);
  const expected = sha256=${hmac.digest('hex')};
  return crypto.timingSafeEqual(
    Buffer.from(expected),
    Buffer.from(signature)
  );
}

Browser Usage:

Browser configuration:
const client = new NovaCLI({
  apiKey: 'nova_pk_abc123...',  // Public key for browser
  enableCORS: true
});

Note: Use public API keys in browser environments.

Request Cancellation:

AbortController support:
const controller = new AbortController();

const promise = client.deployments.list({
  signal: controller.signal
});

// Cancel request
controller.abort();

Retry Configuration:

Custom retry strategy:
const client = new NovaCLI({
  apiKey: 'nova_sk_abc123...',
  retry: {
    retries: 3,
    retryDelay: attemptCount => Math.pow(2, attemptCount) * 1000,
    retryCondition: error => error.response?.status >= 500
  }
});

Interceptors:

Request interceptor:
client.interceptors.request.use(config => {
  console.log('Making request:', config.url);
  return config;
});

Response interceptor:
client.interceptors.response.use(
  response => {
    console.log('Response received:', response.status);
    return response;
  },
  error => {
    console.error('Request failed:', error.message);
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);

NovaCLI provides a GraphQL API as an alternative to REST for flexible data querying. This reference covers the GraphQL schema, query patterns, and best practices.

GraphQL Endpoint:

Single endpoint for all operations:

POST https://api.novacli.io/graphql

Authentication via header:
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY

GraphQL Playground:

Interactive explorer:
https://api.novacli.io/graphql/playground

Schema Introspection:

Query schema:
query IntrospectionQuery {
  __schema {
    queryType { name }
    mutationType { name }
    types {
      name
      kind
      description
    }
  }
}

Basic Queries:

List deployments:
query {
  deployments(status: ACTIVE, limit: 10) {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        name
        status
        region
        createdAt
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      hasNextPage
      endCursor
    }
  }
}

Get single deployment:
query {
  deployment(id: "dep-abc123") {
    id
    name
    status
    region
    size
    config {
      maxConnections
      backupEnabled
    }
    metrics {
      cpu
      memory
      connections
    }
  }
}

Nested Queries:

Deployment with backups:
query {
  deployment(id: "dep-abc123") {
    id
    name
    backups(type: MANUAL, first: 5) {
      edges {
        node {
          id
          createdAt
          sizeBytes
          status
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

Mutations:

Create deployment:
mutation {
  createDeployment(input: {
    name: "my-deployment"
    size: MEDIUM
    region: US_EAST_1
    config: {
      maxConnections: 100
      backupEnabled: true
    }
  }) {
    deployment {
      id
      name
      status
    }
    errors {
      field
      message
    }
  }
}

Update deployment:
mutation {
  updateDeployment(input: {
    id: "dep-abc123"
    size: LARGE
    config: {
      maxConnections: 200
    }
  }) {
    deployment {
      id
      size
      config {
        maxConnections
      }
    }
  }
}

Delete deployment:
mutation {
  deleteDeployment(input: {
    id: "dep-abc123"
    force: false
  }) {
    success
    message
  }
}

Fragments:

Reusable fragments:
fragment DeploymentDetails on Deployment {
  id
  name
  status
  region
  size
  createdAt
}

query {
  deployment(id: "dep-abc123") {
    ...DeploymentDetails
    config {
      maxConnections
    }
  }
}

Variables:

Parameterized queries:
query GetDeployment($id: ID!) {
  deployment(id: $id) {
    id
    name
    status
  }
}

Variables:
{
  "id": "dep-abc123"
}

Pagination:

Cursor-based pagination:
query {
  deployments(first: 10, after: "cursor123") {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        name
      }
      cursor
    }
    pageInfo {
      hasNextPage
      hasPreviousPage
      startCursor
      endCursor
    }
    totalCount
  }
}

Filtering:

Complex filters:
query {
  deployments(
    filter: {
      status: { in: [ACTIVE, STOPPED] }
      region: { eq: US_EAST_1 }
      createdAt: { gte: "2024-09-01" }
    }
    orderBy: { field: CREATED_AT, direction: DESC }
  ) {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        name
      }
    }
  }
}

Subscriptions:

Real-time updates:
subscription {
  deploymentUpdated(id: "dep-abc123") {
    id
    status
    metrics {
      cpu
      memory
    }
  }
}

WebSocket connection required for subscriptions.

Error Handling:

GraphQL errors:
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "message": "Deployment not found",
      "locations": [{"line": 2, "column": 3}],
      "path": ["deployment"],
      "extensions": {
        "code": "NOT_FOUND",
        "deploymentId": "dep-invalid"
      }
    }
  ],
  "data": null
}

Batching:

Batch multiple queries:
query {
  dep1: deployment(id: "dep-abc123") {
    id
    name
  }
  dep2: deployment(id: "dep-xyz789") {
    id
    name
  }
}

Single request returns both deployments.

Field Selection:

Request only needed fields:
query {
  deployments {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        name
      }
    }
  }
}

Reduces payload size and improves performance.

Type System:

Enum types:
enum DeploymentStatus {
  CREATING
  ACTIVE
  STOPPED
  FAILED
  DELETED
}

Enum values used in queries and mutations.

Scalar types:
- ID: Unique identifier
- String: Text
- Int: Integer
- Float: Decimal
- Boolean: true/false
- DateTime: ISO 8601 timestamp

Query Complexity:

Complexity limits prevent expensive queries:
- Maximum depth: 10 levels
- Maximum complexity: 1000 points
- List limits: 100 items per field

Exceeding limits returns error:
{
  "errors": [{
    "message": "Query complexity exceeds maximum",
    "extensions": {
      "code": "QUERY_TOO_COMPLEX",
      "complexity": 1250,
      "maximum": 1000
    }
  }]
}

NovaCLI v3.1 introduces a streamlined approach to configuring SCRAM-SHA-256 authentication for read-only database users. This guide walks through the current best practice for securing user access without requiring manual edits to configuration files.

SCRAM-SHA-256 is a challenge-response authentication mechanism that provides stronger password security compared to legacy MD5 methods. For read-only users who need to query databases without write privileges, proper authentication configuration is critical to maintaining the principle of least privilege.

To configure SCRAM-SHA-256 for a read-only user in NovaCLI v3.1, use the ALTER SYSTEM command to modify authentication settings dynamically:

First, create the read-only user with SCRAM-SHA-256 as the password method:

CREATE ROLE readonly_user WITH LOGIN PASSWORD 'secure_password';
ALTER ROLE readonly_user SET scram_iterations = 4096;

Next, configure the authentication method system-wide:

ALTER SYSTEM SET password_encryption = 'scram-sha-256';
ALTER SYSTEM SET auth_method_readonly = 'scram-sha-256';

Reload the configuration to apply changes:

nova settings reload

Finally, grant read-only permissions to the appropriate databases:

GRANT CONNECT ON DATABASE production TO readonly_user;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA public TO readonly_user;
GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO readonly_user;

This approach eliminates the need to manually edit pg_hba.conf or other configuration files, reducing the risk of syntax errors and making authentication changes auditable through the system catalog. The ALTER SYSTEM method is the recommended approach for NovaCLI v3.x and provides compatibility with containerized deployments where configuration file access may be restricted.

For troubleshooting connection issues, verify that the client application supports SCRAM-SHA-256 and that the password was hashed correctly during user creation.
